Key Match Events: Jos Buttler c Cummins b Zampa 42 (England 92-2)
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler: 'They came out with a lot of intent and put us under a lot of pressure straightaway.'
Jos Buttler: 'Hindsight gives you lots of decisions you could have changed, it was quite extreme conditions with the short side and the wind.'

Adam Zampa: 'We’ve also trained here and know the dimensions. There was a massive breeze so it was about getting England hitting to the long boundary where it is more difficult to hit sixes and fours.'
Mitchell Marsh: 'Experienced guys really stood up when I needed them'
Miscellaneous Highlights: England under a little bit of pressure now.
Very plausible that Scotland and Australia go into their final group game knowing that a Scotland defeat within a certain margin would see both go through and knock England out.
England’s white ball goose is rotating on the spit.
A big week coming up for Messrs Buttler and Mott.
Adam Zampa is player of the match, deservedly so.
Others: England win the toss and bowl!
England were looking for a statement performance. Unfortunately not one like this
